<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1302,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1374,1400]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[762,851,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[762,851,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[908,1051,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[908,1051,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1068,1138,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[177,1422,239,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[151,1435,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1-8. Bellulia spp., adults. 1. B. kareni (after Fibiger 2008); 2. B. tenebrosa sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 3. B. clara sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 4. B. mariannae (after Fibiger 2008); 5. B. parabella (after Fibiger 2008); 6. B. hanae (after Fibiger 2008); 7. B. jiaxuanae sp. n., holotype, China; 8. B. bibella (after Fibiger et al. 2011)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561449/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by paler brown mixed and cyan ground colour of forewing (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[850,937,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[850,937,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is more cyan-brown, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[1231,1372,1411,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[1231,1372,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
more brown); the antemedial line is smooth, arched (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[726,815,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[726,815,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is double, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[1000,1143,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[1000,1143,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- waved); the postmedial line is broader, with a black patch near the costal area (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[810,898,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[810,898,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[955,1097,1483,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[955,1097,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is blackish brown, its inner line appears as a black dot near the costa). In the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[901,1009,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiayiae">
<emphasis box="[901,1009,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiayiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1025,1108,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 23-28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[165,1404,198,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1435,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23-28. Bellulia spp., male genitalia. 23. B. bibella (after Fibiger et al. 2011); 24. B. jiayiae sp. n., holotype, China, genit. prep. hhl-3534-1; 25. B. bella (after Fibiger 2008); 26. B. kendricki (after Fibiger 2010); 27. B. suffusa (after Fibiger 2008); 28. B. basalia (after Fibiger 2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561459" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561459/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), the ventral part of the tegumen fused to the fultura superior with two processes, the left swollen and slightly triangular apically the right with liguliform bend apically (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[470,558,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[470,558,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
these processes strong, left finger-like extended and flattened apically, and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,292,1627,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the left process is rounded apically, and the right is irregularly trifid apically); the left sacculus is narrower and longer than the right, about 1/2 as long as valva (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[851,938,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[851,938,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the left sacculus is narrow, about half of the length of the valva; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[402,543,1699,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[402,543,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is broader and longer, as long as the valva); right ampulla ovoid (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[1327,1414,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[1327,1414,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is elongate and rounded apically, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[551,692,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[551,692,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is bar-shaped); the aedeagus has a large swollen curved coecum, (most swollen in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[390,478,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[390,478,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[597,685,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[597,685,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is slightly swollen, moderate in length, and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[1243,1385,1771,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[1243,1385,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is narrow, small and waved), the terminal part of the aedeagus smoothly curved, not raised dorsally (in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2008" box="[1298,1386,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis box="[1298,1386,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is slightly curved and ta[ers apically; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Han &amp; Kononenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[574,715,1843,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Bellulia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiaxuanae">
<emphasis box="[574,715,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">B. jiaxuanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is bent at a right angle, and smoothly raised dorsally).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1302,2013]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,801]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,415,1878,1904]" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Discription. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[433,503,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 9-16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[180,1435,338,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-89@4.[151,1435,309,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9-16. Bellulia spp., adults. 9. B. jiayiae sp. n., holotype, China; 10. B. bella (after Fibiger 2008); 11. B. kendricki (after Fibiger 2010); 12. B. suffusa (after Fibiger 2008); 13. B. basalia (after Fibiger 2010); 14. B. fuscis sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 15. B. diannana sp. n., holotype, Cambodia; 16. B. wui (after Fibiger 2008)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561451/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="123">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 11.0-12.2 mm. Head, thorax and abdomen greyish brown, with black scales on patagium, black line at centre of meso- and metathorax, and black tufts of scales at two basal segmens of abdomen. Forewing brownish grey with cyan and black; basal line black, thin, expressed only in costal margin; antemedial line black, double, smoothly curved, with outer line broader and more distinct than inner one; postmedial line black, thin, double, excurved from costa to inner margin of discal cell, then incurved towards inner margin of wing, two fused lines form black C-mark in costal area; subterminal line black, formed by irregular spots between costa and M2, othrewise indistinct; terminal line black; fringe same as ground colour, mixed greyish yellow basally; costal area smoky-black with cyan and scattered whitish-grey scales and darker reminder of wing; reniform spot oblate, muddy yellow, slightly oblique. Hindwing lighter than forewing; discal spot present, tinged, dark; outer margin slightly angular at CuA1; fringe same as ground colour, mixed greyish yellow basally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,801]" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,358,385]" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[384,469,359,385]" captionStart="FIGURES 23-28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[165,1404,198,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1435,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 23-28. Bellulia spp., male genitalia. 23. B. bibella (after Fibiger et al. 2011); 24. B. jiayiae sp. n., holotype, China, genit. prep. hhl-3534-1; 25. B. bella (after Fibiger 2008); 26. B. kendricki (after Fibiger 2010); 27. B. suffusa (after Fibiger 2008); 28. B. basalia (after Fibiger 2010)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561459" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561459/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Tegumen narrow, about twice as long as vinculum fused ventrally to fultura superior, bearing prominent, log-shaped curved process on each side, left e longer than right and with swollen and slightly triangular apex, the right with liguliform bended apex, basal part of right process broader than that of left. Vinculum broader than tegumen, V-shaped. Saccus hardly thick, V-shaped. Juxta walnut-shaped, sclerotized, with circular opening in center. Valvae narrow, asymmetrical, left shorter than right; sacculi asymmetrical, left narrower and longer than right, 1/2 as long as valva, right sacculus broad, 1/3 as long as valva; ampullae asymmetrical, curved, with heavy setae, right one largerr and broader than left, apically ovoid, left sacculus apically bar-shaped; costa thick, arched, left broader than right. Aedeagus with coecum about 1/7 as long as aedeagus; its posterior half gently curved; ductus ejaculatorius slightly swollen; vesica with four tiny sclerotized cornuti.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,801]" box="[199,611,670,697]" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,396,670,697]" pageId="7" pageNumber="124">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
